result.execSummary:
The defendant Gary L Meenen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Gary L Meenen is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Gary L Meenen was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse - Infliction of Physical Pain or Injury, Repeater, Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Gary L Meenen was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse - Infliction of Physical Pain or Injury, Repeater, Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Revoked, sentenced to county jail/HOC - 01/16/2015
By Atty Jeanne Zamzow

1:16 p.m.  State by ADA Lisa Vanden Branden.  Defendant present, in custody, with Attorney Reisha Mitchell.

Attorney Mitchell recites the agreement - defendant to plea to counts 3 and 4, as charged in the Information - State will be moving to dismiss the remaining counts.  ADA concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of the offenses - with domestic abuse enhancers and as a repeater.   Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties and as a repeater.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to counts 3 and 4 - domestic abuse and as a repeater.  Court finds the pleas are made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support each plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to counts 3 and 4, as charged and orders a judgment of conviction be entered today.  Court dismisses counts 1 and 2.

ADA confirms compliance with any victim/witness rights.  Sentencing statement by ADA.  Senttencing argument by Attorney Mitchell.  No statement by the defendant.

Each count - Sentenced to 6 months county jail consecutive to any other sentence, stayed and placed on 2 years of probation.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
Complete AODA
NO violent contact with Andrea W.
Maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess/consume any alcohol, illegal drugs, or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
To be at no place that serves alcohol by-the-drink.
Complete a domestic violence assessment and comply with any recommended follow-up.
Maintain sexual offender registry.
Pay court costs.
Abide with all other rules/recommendations as imposed by the supervising agent.

If jail to be served may be served in another county and with huber.  Court grants the defendant 14 days of sentence credit.
